Banro Corporation has entered a definitive agreement to sell its Namoya Mining SA operating mine to a consortium of investors that includes Baiyin International Investment and Shomka Resources. In exchange, Banro will receive a perpetual royalty for all production from the Namoya property. The transaction is still subject to certain conditions, including final approval from the Democratic Republic of Congo government. The buyer will assume management control of the Company with immediate effect, and planning will commence immediately in an effort to re-start the mining operations as soon as possible. Read more about goldMultimedia: Webinar series: Digital DRC Mining Week 17-19 June 2020